
Note: Download and install redis before running this program, please refer to http://redis.io/download

Prerequisite:
go get github.com/mediocregopher/radix.v2/cluster
go get github.com/mediocregopher/radix.v2/redis

Download:
git clone git@github.com:mllu/redisCluster.git

Directory Tree
.
|____conf
| |____7001
| |____7002
| |____7003
| |____7004
| |____7005
| |____7006
|____lib

1. conf
  -- config files to set up simple redis cluster
  usage: run `redis-server CONFIG_FILE` for each subdirectory

2. lib
  -- go util for level-logging
  
To set up cluster by joining master & slave
  usage:
      go run redisCluster.go

